&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Rotational Pharmacy Technician&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 4&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Croydon Health Services is a newly formed integrated care organisation created on 1st August 2010 providing hospital and community services from a number of locations throughout Croydon. The Trust comprises the former Croydon Community Health Services and Mayday Healthcare NHS Trust. Around 3,500 staff provides services for a population of over 340,000 people from diverse community groups.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are currently looking for a motivated team player with an active interest in all aspects of patient care to work on rotation between the dispensary, stores /distribution, wards and technical services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This rotation allows the opportunity to work in different areas of pharmacy in order to choose the suitable specialty for further career development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful applicant will also participate in the development of ward based services after completion of all relevant training in dispensary, stores/distribution and technical services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants should hold NVQ Level 3 diploma in Pharmacy Service skills (QCF) or equivalent and approved underpinning knowledge BTEC National Diploma in Pharmacy Services (City &amp; Guilds) or equivalent recognized Pharmacy Technician qualification and must be registered with the GPhC general pharmaceutical council.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You should be enthusiastic, motivated and keen to develop your skills further. The pharmacy department actively encourages continuous professional development, education and training.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful applicant will contribute to late duty and weekend working.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applications from newly qualified or current student technicians are welcome.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interviews: Week commencing 1st December 2020.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;To discuss this post or to arrange an informal visit please contact Shagufta Ali on 0208 401 3000 ext 5911 or via email: Shagufta.ali1@nhs.net&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
